Package: mcplr
Version: 0.1-0
Date: 2008-05-19
Title: Multiple Cue Probability Learning in R
Author: Maarten Speekenbrink <m.speekenbrink@ucl.ac.uk>
Maintainer: Maarten Speekenbrink <m.speekenbrink@ucl.ac.uk>
Depends: R (>= 2.6.0), stats4, methods
Description: mcplR offers a flexible (S4) framework to investigate multiple cue probability learning (MCPL). 
  mcplR incorporates a number of learning models (Rescorla-Wagner, GCM, ALCOVE, etc) in a general state-space framework, 
  where new models can be easily added.
Collate: allGenerics.R classes.R bdiag.R relist.R mcplprepare.R RatioRuleResponse.R GaussianMixtureResponse.R GaussianResponse.R GCM.R SLFN.R
License: GPL (>=2)
URL: http://mcplr.r-forge.r-project.org/
